In [3]:
def parse_df(files, name):
    dfs = [pd.read_csv(path + f) for f in files]
    dfs = [df[["Location ID", "Location", "Value"]] for df in dfs]
    for df, year in zip(dfs, [2018, 2019, 2020]):
        df["Year"] = year
    df_res = pd.concat(dfs) 
    return df_res.sort_values(by=["Location ID", "Location", "Year"]).rename(columns={"Value": name})

# avg temperature
df_tavg = parse_df(t_avg, "Temp Avg")

In [7]:
# put together 
df_climate = df_tavg.merge(df_tmax, on = ["Location ID", "Location", "Year"])\
                    .merge(df_tmin, on = ["Location ID", "Location", "Year"])\
                    .merge(df_pcp, on = ["Location ID", "Location", "Year"])
df_climate["Location ID"] = df_climate["Location ID"].apply(lambda x:x[:2])
df_climate = df_climate.rename(columns={"Location ID": "State", "Location": "County"})
df_climate["Location"] = df_climate["County"] + ", " + df_climate["State"] 
df_climate.head(10)

# Top 10 coldest counties in the Winter of 2019
plot_data = df_climate[df_climate["Year"] == 2019][["Location", "Temp Min"]]\
            .sort_values(by = "Temp Min", ascending = True)\
            .head(10)

plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
sns.barplot(data = plot_data, y = "Location", x = "Temp Min", orient = 'h').set(
    xlabel = "Temp Min",
    ylabel = "Location",
    title = "Top 10 coldest counties in the Winter of 2019"
)
plt.show()
